    proc generate_node with context, condition
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 8, indent_level

    proc emit_right_paren from Emitter with emitter
    proc emit_space from Emitter with emitter
    proc emit_script_block_start from Emitter with emitter
    proc emit_newline from Emitter with emitter

    Note: Body
    proc increase_indent from context
    Let body be proc get_dict_hir_value with hir, "body"
    proc generate_node with context, body
    proc emit_newline from Emitter with emitter
    proc decrease_indent from context

    proc emit_indent from Emitter with emitter, indent_level
    proc emit_script_block_end from Emitter with emitter

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
PowerShell `for (init; cond; update) { body }` uses three semicolon-
separated expression slots. Each slot is dispatched with indent zeroed
so they remain on one line; the body block then gets normal indented
treatment.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-guards hir. Emits indent + `for (`. For each of "initialization",
"condition", "update": saves indent to 0, dispatches the subtree,
restores indent, and emits `; ` between the first two and before the
closing paren after the third. Emits `) {`, newline, indented body via
generate_node, newline, dedented `}`.
@End Implementation
