    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 8, indent_level

    proc emit_right_paren from Emitter with emitter
    proc emit_space from Emitter with emitter
    proc emit_script_block_start from Emitter with emitter
    proc emit_newline from Emitter with emitter

    Note: Body
    proc increase_indent from context
    Let body be proc get_dict_hir_value with hir, "body"
    proc generate_node with context, body
    proc emit_newline from Emitter with emitter
    proc decrease_indent from context

    proc emit_indent from Emitter with emitter, indent_level
    proc emit_script_block_end from Emitter with emitter

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
PowerShell's `foreach ($var in $collection) { body }` is the canonical
collection-iteration form. The loop variable is emitted with its sigil
via emit_variable so its appearance in the body matches user code style.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-guards hir. Emits indent + `foreach (`. Reads the "variable" string
and emits `$<variable>` via emit_variable. Emits ` in `. Saves indent
to 0, dispatches "collection", restores indent. Emits `) {` newline,
indented body via generate_node, newline, dedented `}`.
@End Implementation
